Run VS Code as Administrator

Check node and npm versions

> node -v
>> npm cache clean -f
>> npm install -g n
> npm install -g npm@latest

> npm i -g generator-aspnetcore-spa
> yo aspnetcore-spa

Name the application using Camel Case

> dotnet build
> dotnet run

Check the Console in the browser's developer tools to see if [HMR] connected message is displayed.
If you decide to run your application by executing dotnet run you may notice that HMR is not be
enabled, this is because you are not passing “Development” as the environment variable. If you
want to run the application in Development mode, execute the following command:

> dotnet run — environment=”Development”